Here is a concise JavaScript function using ES6 syntax:

```javascript
function sumArr(arr) {
  return arr.reduce((sum, x) => sum + Number(x), 0);
}

module.exports = { sumArr };
```

In this code, `reduce()` method executes the provided callback function on each element in the array from left to right. If there is no initial value defined (which is our case here), it assigns first array item as it. Then, it returns all accumulated result which will be our total sum of numbers. By default, elements that are not number type are converted to Number before addition by specifying `x` inside `Number()`.

